# **1\. Install JDK (Java Development Kit)**

Java must be installed before running the project.

## **1.1 Install Homebrew (recommended)**

Open **Terminal** and run:

`/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"`

## **1.2 Install JDK (Temurin 17 recommended)**

`brew install --cask temurin`

This will install the latest LTS JDK version for macOS.

## **1.3 Verify Java Installation**

Run:

`java -version`  
`javac -version`

Expected output (may vary slightly):

`openjdk version "17.0.x" ...`  
`OpenJDK Runtime Environment (Temurin)`  
`OpenJDK 64-Bit Server VM`

If both commands show a version number, Java is installed correctly.

# **2\. Configure Environment Variables (if needed)**

Most macOS Homebrew installations configure Java automatically.  
 But if `java` or `javac` commands do not work, add Java to your PATH.

### **2.1 Find JDK installation path**

`/usr/libexec/java_home -V`

You will see something like:

`/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-17.jdk/Contents/Home`

### **2.2 Add JDK to PATH**

Edit your `.zshrc`:

`nano ~/.zshrc`

Add:

`export JAVA_HOME="/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-17.jdk/Contents/Home"`  
`export PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:$PATH"`

Reload terminal:

`source ~/.zshrc`

Check again:

`java -version`  
`javac -version`

# **6\. Compile and Run Using VS Code**

### **6.1 How to Build**

VS Code automatically compiles Java files when the Java extension pack is installed.

To manually compile using terminal:

`cd src`  
`javac com/airtripe/studentmanagement/Main.java`

If no errors appear, compilation is successful.
